public class Solution extends GuessGame {
    public int guessNumber(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = n; i >= 1; i--) {
            if (guess(i) == 1) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

efficiency: MEDIUM
time complexity: O(log(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution uses a for loop to iterate from n to 1. For each iteration, it calls the guess() function to check if the guessed number is higher than the picked number. If the result is 1, it increments the count. After iterating through all numbers from n to 1, the function returns the count. The efficiency is considered medium because the algorithm has a logarithmic time complexity (O(log(n)) due to the iterative approach. The space complexity is O(1) since only a constant amount of memory is used, and the energy implications are low as the algorithm does not involve any resource-intensive operations.

